{"id":14881073,"mediaExerciseId":"9c5c62f4-30bc-41bd-bf90-d45d71ebca1d","exerciseName":"24","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612313,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":235,"solutions":[{"id":6014812,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **we should determine the dirty price by using the clean price and the coupon rate.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/534762b3ccceee14e37e1716e8370353/743e1ac896f2101b04eeff691f720be6/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/534762b3ccceee14e37e1716e8370353/743e1ac896f2101b04eeff691f720be6/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The clean price is the bond price without including any interest within. On the contrary, a dirty price is a price that contains accumulated interest. If we subtract the clean price from the dirty price, we will get the amount of the collected interest.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":136,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/534762b3ccceee14e37e1716e8370353/ecfaa76fcb630093c2b0c32f1b64a392/lateximg_large.png","width":999},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/534762b3ccceee14e37e1716e8370353/ecfaa76fcb630093c2b0c32f1b64a392/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"We should first calculate the value of the accrued interest. Let's consider that the year has 360 days. Because the coupon payments are semiannual, one payout is for 180 days. We have two months left until the next payout. It is 60 days. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/534762b3ccceee14e37e1716e8370353/b6b7991484561f226199c16d8f41aeac/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/534762b3ccceee14e37e1716e8370353/b6b7991484561f226199c16d8f41aeac/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The accrued interest we should calculate for the days that passed (120 days). The par value of the bond is not written. Let's assume it is 1000. Let's calculate collected interest by using the following formula. \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{accrued interest}&=\\text{par value}\\times\\dfrac{\\text{annual interest}}{2}\\times\\dfrac{120}{180}\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\$1,000\\times\\dfrac{5.3\\%}{2}\\times0.666\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\boxed{\\$17.667}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe accrued interest is \\$17.667.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":459,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/534762b3ccceee14e37e1716e8370353/311022e312cdfce9b102abea01195169/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"regular":{"height":231,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/534762b3ccceee14e37e1716e8370353/311022e312cdfce9b102abea01195169/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"To get the dirty price, we should add the calculated accrued interest to the clean amount of the bond.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{dirty price}&=\\$17.667+\\$951\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\$968.667\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The dirty price of the bond is \\$968.167.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":275,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/534762b3ccceee14e37e1716e8370353/dc7b159f8325b89700b4446921ac5f2e/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":139,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/534762b3ccceee14e37e1716e8370353/dc7b159f8325b89700b4446921ac5f2e/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"3dc6e07c-895f-4d84-bb0e-036d581f91be","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881074,"exerciseName":"25","page":235,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"1e682aab-a47e-4ace-add1-0aee4fa52cda","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-25-1e682aab-a47e-4ace-add1-0aee4fa52cda"},{"id":14881075,"exerciseName":"26","page":235,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"707583c1-16ff-41a8-aa5d-80fe68ee5892","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-26-707583c1-16ff-41a8-aa5d-80fe68ee5892"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881072,"exerciseName":"23","page":235,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"60fc1d34-054a-4406-b757-b235371b0437","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-23-60fc1d34-054a-4406-b757-b235371b0437"},{"id":14881071,"exerciseName":"22","page":2